1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,240
It's exciting to be a part of Yorba Linda First Baptist Church and mothering that church 40 years ago.

2
00:00:06,820 --> 00:00:12,040
And Joe Guthrie was the pastor at that time, and Joe, friends, is not doing well.

3
00:00:13,070 --> 00:00:17,350
Joe is very close to going home to the Lord, and he knows that, and Maureen knows that.

4
00:00:17,610 --> 00:00:24,590
I went to see him just a couple days ago, and some days are up, some days are low, but he is ready to be with Jesus.

5
00:00:24,590 --> 00:00:29,370
But he also wants to be at that celebration that's taking place in about 20 minutes.

6
00:00:30,110 --> 00:00:34,890
And so I want us just to pray for a moment for Joe, for his strength, that he can go to that.

7
00:00:35,530 --> 00:00:37,370
And I also want to pray for Myra Riemann.

8
00:00:37,650 --> 00:00:38,470
Tim is out here.

9
00:00:39,010 --> 00:00:42,350
Myra has just undergone open-heart surgery on Friday.

10
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:47,550
She is a young gal, and they took out a great big tumor out of her heart.

11
00:00:47,990 --> 00:00:53,750
It has been a major surgery, and God was faithful to the Riemann family all the way through.

12
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:56,090
And it's been a miracle, and she's doing very well.

13
00:00:56,410 --> 00:00:58,330
We want to praise the Lord for that as well.

14
00:00:58,330 --> 00:01:00,430
So it is good to see you in church, my friend.

15
00:01:00,850 --> 00:01:04,690
That's a miracle, and God has blessed that family in some powerful ways.

16
00:01:04,950 --> 00:01:07,390
Let's begin our time with just a word of prayer for Joe and for Myra.

17
00:01:07,490 --> 00:01:13,770
Father, as a church, this is family, and we come before you thanking you for the miracle

18
00:01:13,770 --> 00:01:17,010
that we've seen as you worked in Myra's life in the past few days.

19
00:01:17,310 --> 00:01:22,590
We thank you that your spirit has been so evident and so powerful in that family and

20
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:23,970
with her and her body.

21
00:01:24,370 --> 00:01:28,190
We thank you those doctors were able to get in there and take that out, that her heart

22
00:01:28,190 --> 00:01:34,430
is beating normally and that she is feeling as good as can be expected given all the trauma to

23
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:41,610
her body she has experienced. But she was smiling yesterday and praising you and we do too. And thank

24
00:01:41,610 --> 00:01:47,350
you for carrying Tim through the process as a faithful husband all the way. Now bless him with

25
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:53,810
rest. Bless Myra with rest and the family that has been so diligent by her side. Give them comfort

26
00:01:53,810 --> 00:01:56,850
and Lord, bring her back soon to worship with us, we pray.

27
00:01:57,450 --> 00:01:58,930
And Father, I thank you for Joe,

28
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:02,160
for his faithful ministry for so many years,

29
00:02:02,540 --> 00:02:05,540
for starting our sister church just down the road,

30
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:06,480
the next community.

31
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,300
Father, this morning I pray

32
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:10,800
that you would give him a supernatural burst of energy

33
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,680
that he might go and be a part of that celebration

34
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,820
and receive the joy of knowing

35
00:02:15,820 --> 00:02:17,660
that you called him 40 years ago

36
00:02:17,660 --> 00:02:19,460
to start that experience

37
00:02:19,460 --> 00:02:22,200
and to see what great things you have done

38
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,040
through all of that.

39
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:25,740
So bless he and Maureen this morning, we pray.

40
00:02:26,260 --> 00:02:33,200
We thank you for the opportunity we have to come alongside a church and a family and to pray for them.

41
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,240
So hear our prayers, we pray.

42
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:36,380
We love you.

43
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:37,780
We thank you that we can pray.

44
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:40,420
And we ask these things in Jesus' name.

45
00:02:41,290 --> 00:02:41,810
And amen.

46
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,040
Amen.

47
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:50,460
Well, as we enter into the very last part of our campaign in Owning the Vision,

48
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:55,650
this message as well is family business.

49
00:02:56,530 --> 00:02:58,110
And if you are a guest with us,

50
00:02:58,150 --> 00:03:00,730
if you came at Easter and you've come as part of that,

51
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:02,310
or you've come with a friend this morning,

52
00:03:02,670 --> 00:03:06,120
I just want to say to you, this is not for you.

53
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:10,110
You can just relax and enjoy.

54
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:12,370
I know that what we're going to talk about,

55
00:03:12,410 --> 00:03:13,470
I think will bless you.

56
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:16,090
And I think there'll be some great challenge for you,

57
00:03:16,090 --> 00:03:17,810
but it's not for you.

58
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:19,350
So you just relax.

59
00:03:19,470 --> 00:03:20,910
But this is a family discussion

60
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:23,690
about owning the vision, about our giving,

61
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,890
about what the Lord would have for us.

62
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:30,050
Three years ago, as I mentioned, we started what we call building up.

63
00:03:30,670 --> 00:03:33,070
And we renovated the facilities in this room.

64
00:03:33,770 --> 00:03:37,390
We put in all new, the new seats that you have are sitting on,

65
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,790
the new carpets, the new sound system.

66
00:03:40,350 --> 00:03:45,330
We built the new stage, put some lights in the room next door.

67
00:03:45,450 --> 00:03:49,530
We gutted out that beautiful, beautiful, it was a beautiful box

68
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:51,090
but had really run its course.

69
00:03:51,390 --> 00:03:54,670
Our gymnasium next door, we've made it into a multi-purpose room.

70
00:03:55,170 --> 00:03:59,470
We scraped out the basement and made it a coffee bar and Starbucks down there

71
00:03:59,470 --> 00:04:01,670
and weight room and internet and all that stuff.

72
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:03,710
If you haven't been there, you need to see that.

73
00:04:04,510 --> 00:04:06,930
And the Lord allowed us to have a wonderful elevator

74
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:09,690
that Betty rides in when nobody's looking, as she shared.

75
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:13,100
And we're so thankful for all these wonderful things.

76
00:04:13,340 --> 00:04:15,480
It has been an amazing project in three years,

77
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:17,180
and now we're going to continue to pay for that

78
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:19,460
and pay down the loan as fast as we can.

79
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:24,280
And so that's what this message kind of leads us into next week is our banquet

80
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,520
as we celebrate the good things God has done,

81
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:30,120
and then we take our next set of commitments to pay down that loan

82
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,680
and wipe it out in the next three to six years.

83
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:37,220
So with that, I want to share again God's heart for our stewardship.

84
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:41,600
And I heard a story about a pastor, and I relate to this,

85
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,900
who had preached eight sermons on giving.

86
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,900
Can you imagine suffering through that?

87
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:52,130
And they finally said, Pastor, when are you going to stop preaching on giving?

88
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,790
And he said, when you start giving.

89
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,110
Now this is my last one.

90
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,580
Dan Jackson will be here next week.

91
00:05:02,420 --> 00:05:03,860
But I want to review a few things.

92
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:11,620
We established a connection in weeks past between our soul and our possessions.

93
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:17,040
We established the connection because Jesus established that connection.

94
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:23,740
He said this, where your treasure is, there your heart and your thoughts will be.

95
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:30,520
He knew that where our treasure was, that's what our heart would beat for.

96
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:32,340
That's what we'd be excited for.

97
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,060
That's where our commitments would be.

98
00:05:35,050 --> 00:05:38,530
And he knew that how we treat our stuff is a relationship to how we treat God.

99
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:47,780
Our giving, friends, is a direct reflection of our spiritual maturity.

100
00:05:48,970 --> 00:05:50,930
It took me a long time to figure that out.

101
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:54,650
The verses were all there, but I never saw the connection.

102
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:59,580
But when I began to really give unto the Lord,

103
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:03,480
I noticed that in my own spirit, I learned some things about trust,

104
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,260
about who I was in Christ.

105
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:09,400
I learned to appreciate the good things I have, the clothes on my back.

106
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:12,500
And I also began to not worry as much about those things.

107
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:16,920
As I grew in faith, I had a better perspective on my things.

108
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:20,740
and it came as a result of prying away

109
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:23,240
some of the money that I held on to

110
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,880
and saying, Lord, I trust you.

111
00:06:26,340 --> 00:06:28,760
And it wasn't an easy issue for me.

112
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,200
I was rationalized.

113
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,820
But Lord, I'm giving my time.

114
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,300
I'm so poor right now,

115
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,500
especially in seminary.

116
00:06:37,780 --> 00:06:38,660
We had nothing.

117
00:06:41,410 --> 00:06:42,710
But we started to give.

118
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:45,240
God carried us.

119
00:06:46,450 --> 00:06:47,170
It was amazing.

120
00:06:48,230 --> 00:06:49,930
And out of trusting Him, we gave more.

121
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,920
We have struggled with this journey.

122
00:06:54,410 --> 00:06:57,310
But I realize, and I see it in Scripture now very clearly,

123
00:06:57,870 --> 00:07:02,530
that how we relate to our things is directly related to how we relate to God.

124
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:04,360
We are so connected.

125
00:07:05,670 --> 00:07:10,950
And we discovered that as we pump up and change our heart, we can change our giving.

126
00:07:11,330 --> 00:07:12,950
Changing our giving changes our heart.

127
00:07:12,950 --> 00:07:16,110
And so I've entitled this message, Pump Up the Volume.

128
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:20,150
And I don't mean in your car with your bass speakers going thump, thump.

129
00:07:21,630 --> 00:07:23,690
I mean pump up your heart volume.

130
00:07:24,270 --> 00:07:25,430
And you know how you do that?

131
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:26,820
You give.

132
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:30,170
Your heart grows when you give.

133
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:34,010
Your heart grows when you give.

134
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:38,370
Giving is great because it opens us up to new things about God.

135
00:07:39,330 --> 00:07:42,470
Giving is great because it challenges our materialism,

136
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:44,030
especially in North Orange County.

137
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:48,010
Oh my goodness, we're so inundated with so many good things,

138
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:52,170
but it's easy to get off track and to get interested more in things

139
00:07:52,170 --> 00:07:53,250
than in the things of God.

140
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,960
And a regular giving experience

141
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:58,200
focuses us on what's important.

142
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:01,380
It focuses us on the kingdom.

143
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,560
It freely opens up our souls.

144
00:08:06,140 --> 00:08:08,780
But I also realize that that's wonderful to talk about.

145
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:11,220
I've heard messages on giving for years.

146
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:13,610
And it never hit me.

147
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,980
And I realize something about that

148
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:19,080
that's one thing to know it in our minds,

149
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:22,080
but behavior change is a different matter.

150
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:30,630
When I got convicted a while back, a few years ago, somewhere I realized that this is the only body I've got.

151
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:37,340
You really can't, at this point in our technology, I can't trade in much.

152
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:39,020
This is it.

153
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:45,000
And I realized as a leader and a shepherd and a pastor that I am the tool.

154
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:48,420
And I better be here.

155
00:08:49,490 --> 00:08:53,010
And I better be sharp so that I give you good data.

156
00:08:55,050 --> 00:08:59,270
Because if you come and you have a need and you want me to pray or to teach or to lead,

157
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:03,070
and if my body's falling apart, I'm not giving you the best.

158
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,120
And I realized I need to take care of myself.

159
00:09:09,430 --> 00:09:10,730
And so I began to struggle.

160
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:11,890
I needed to work out.

161
00:09:12,940 --> 00:09:15,080
I needed to get my heart in good shape.

162
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,260
I needed to eat right.

163
00:09:16,340 --> 00:09:17,460
I needed to sleep right.

164
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:20,740
It's easy for me to stay up all night because of the issues,

165
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:28,750
but I have to say no because these people deserve my best, not my worst.

166
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:31,670
And I struggled.

167
00:09:31,790 --> 00:09:33,150
These are behavior changes.

168
00:09:33,370 --> 00:09:36,470
This is now, but Lord, my calendar is so full.

169
00:09:36,630 --> 00:09:38,990
I don't have time to go to a club and work out.

170
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:42,120
I had to carve it out.

171
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:44,820
I had to put it on that calendar.

172
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,820
I'm doing this.

173
00:09:45,980 --> 00:09:49,160
Carol, we're not doing anything else from 4.30 to 6 on these days.

174
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,800
And that bumped a lot of people around.

175
00:09:54,770 --> 00:09:55,970
Behavior change was hard.

176
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:57,570
The patterns were hard.

177
00:09:58,650 --> 00:10:03,670
Going to bed on time was hard because I wanted to do more.

178
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:08,490
Getting rid of McDonald's was hard.

179
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:15,250
And you know, nothing against McDonald's, but I feel a lot better now that I don't go there as much.

180
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,900
My stomach feels better.

181
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:20,700
Do you know what I'm saying?

182
00:10:21,340 --> 00:10:23,080
This is not a slanderous thing on McDonald's.

183
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:26,800
I'm just challenging that sometimes the food we eat isn't good for us.

184
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,400
It gets us by.

185
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:30,560
But those patterns are not healthy.

186
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:33,800
I had to change my patterns and my behavior.

187
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:36,040
Lifestyle choices are hard work.

188
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:39,720
And the same is true with our own stewardship before God.

189
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:43,900
It requires not only a new head, a new heart, but it requires new behaviors.

190
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:46,920
And so this message, I want it to be very practical.

191
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:52,780
I want to share with you some practical tools to help you as you're wrestling with this process.

192
00:10:53,140 --> 00:10:58,520
And I'm indebted to this great material that I pulled out of Wesley Wilmer's book, God and Your Stuff.

193
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:03,160
He's a professor at Talbot right next door, and I love what he has to say.

194
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:08,590
The first thing I want to say, if you want to write this down, this is a good list of nine things

195
00:11:08,590 --> 00:11:10,760
to get real practical.

196
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,520
Number one, if you want to give and honor the Lord

197
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:17,420
and grow in faith and grow in maturity in Christ,

198
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:22,440
declare, number one, who is Lord of your life?

199
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:27,040
And ask the question honestly.

200
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:29,380
Is God the director of your life,

201
00:11:29,380 --> 00:11:32,900
or do your things rule your life?

202
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:37,620
Who is Lord of your life?

203
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:41,450
Does God possess your life,

204
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:44,230
Or do your possessions possess your life?

205
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:48,510
Which do you strive after when you get really honest?

206
00:11:49,950 --> 00:11:52,590
Which one is really most important?

207
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,340
Jesus said it well.

208
00:11:56,650 --> 00:11:57,750
Matthew 6, 24,

209
00:11:57,930 --> 00:12:02,610
No one can serve two masters, for you will hate the one and love the other,

210
00:12:02,790 --> 00:12:05,510
or be devoted to one and despise the other.

211
00:12:05,930 --> 00:12:09,570
You cannot serve both God and money.

212
00:12:11,310 --> 00:12:13,670
One will take precedence over the other.

213
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:20,380
Our challenge is that when you regularly give, it puts God back, number one, in your life.

214
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,400
Who is Lord of your life?

215
00:12:22,620 --> 00:12:25,480
Is the kingdom of God the most important thing to you?

216
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:29,460
Or are you more concerned about the cares of the world?

217
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,620
Declare, friends, who is Lord of your life.

218
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:40,120
Number two is to really understand what a faithful steward really is.

219
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:41,900
What is a faithful steward?

220
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:46,560
A steward is somebody who manages for somebody else.

221
00:12:48,850 --> 00:12:52,870
And if you get honest, you realize your life is not your own.

222
00:12:54,360 --> 00:13:01,370
Jesus gave us life, and in Christ, what he did on the cross, he bought our lives.

223
00:13:01,570 --> 00:13:03,230
We are totally his.

224
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:10,440
And everything we have, all of our talents, our possessions, our ability to make money, our gifts,

225
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:12,940
everything is ultimately his.

226
00:13:12,940 --> 00:13:23,060
we are stewards of our lives we are not the owners of our lives and we will be held accountable

227
00:13:23,060 --> 00:13:33,810
before god for what we did with our lives who owns it all is the question in matthew 25 the

228
00:13:33,810 --> 00:13:39,690
parable of the talents jesus talks about how god gives various gifts to various people

229
00:13:39,690 --> 00:13:46,130
that they might invest them in the kingdom of god and then they're given and held account

230
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:51,100
for what they did and how they used the things God gave them.

231
00:13:54,090 --> 00:13:56,330
Friends, to improve our giving, to improve our heart,

232
00:13:56,410 --> 00:13:58,990
to enlarge our heart, to pump up that heart volume,

233
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:01,930
we're going to have to understand that we are stewards

234
00:14:01,930 --> 00:14:04,290
and to understand what a steward really is,

235
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:06,410
is a manager, not the owner.

236
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:09,620
God owns, we manage.

237
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:12,320
That's number two.

238
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:17,640
Number three on our practical steps towards having blessed giving

239
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,180
is to count your blessings.

240
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:23,860
And to realize that you have more than you think you do.

241
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:31,830
It's a great exercise sometime to get alone and perhaps go down to the beach or the mountains

242
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:38,250
and spend an afternoon just reflecting on how much and in what ways God has blessed your life.

243
00:14:38,630 --> 00:14:44,200
Think about your family, who you have as your family, who you have as your friends.

244
